00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:22,380
and I had to contribute
to my society in a huge way.

1000
00:50:22,452 --> 00:50:26,388
I came up with this idea
of starting a foundation

1001
00:50:26,456 --> 00:50:29,152
where we would actually
reach out

1002
00:50:29,226 --> 00:50:31,888
to children who lost
their mothers and fathers

1003
00:50:31,962 --> 00:50:33,224
to incarceration.

1004
00:50:33,296 --> 00:50:36,094
We provide tutoring,
mentoring.

1005
00:50:36,166 --> 00:50:40,330
I'm gonna ask that each one of
you guys get up and scream out,

1006
00:50:40,404 --> 00:50:43,066
"I am somebody!"

1007
00:50:43,140 --> 00:50:47,076
We connect them
with a positive role model.

1008
00:50:47,144 --> 00:50:49,738
And we transport them up
to these correctional facilities

1009
00:50:49,813 --> 00:50:53,078
so that they can
reestablish the bond

1010
00:50:53,150 --> 00:50:55,345
with their parents.

1011
00:50:55,419 --> 00:50:58,582
How long your dad
been in prison?

1012
00:50:58,655 --> 00:51:00,088
Like, 6 years.

1013
00:51:00,157 --> 00:51:01,556
5 <i>Years?</i>

1014
00:51:01,625 --> 00:51:03,923
When was the last time
you seen your dad?

1015
00:51:03,994 --> 00:51:06,292
Like...2 years ago.

1016
00:51:06,363 --> 00:51:08,422
It's a crying shame
that, you know,

1017
00:51:08,498 --> 00:51:12,434
mass incarceration
had taken over the community

1018
00:51:12,502 --> 00:51:13,867
the way it did, you know.

1019
00:51:13,937 --> 00:51:17,100
And I remain hopeful
that they will soften up

1020
00:51:17,174 --> 00:51:18,607
some of these policies.

1021
00:51:18,675 --> 00:51:21,610
Hopefully some of these parents
can return home

1022
00:51:21,678 --> 00:51:26,342
and, you know, become,
you know, parents again.

1023
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:30,113
GATES: Terrence's efforts
to help these children

1024
00:51:30,187 --> 00:51:32,849
break the cycle
of incarceration

1025
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:36,290
connects him to the most
important unifying thread

1026
00:51:36,359 --> 00:51:39,920
that runs through
black history--

1027
00:51:39,996 --> 00:51:42,794
the enduring will
both to survive

1028
00:51:42,866 --> 00:51:45,630
and to carve out
a better future

1029
00:51:45,702 --> 00:51:48,068
for those who follow.

1030
00:51:55,712 --> 00:51:59,705
KARENGA: Everybody benefited
from our movement.

1031
00:51:59,783 --> 00:52:05,881
Native Americans, Latinos,
Asians, Women, Gays, Seniors

1032
00:52:05,956 --> 00:52:07,617
built on
our conversation.

1033
00:52:07,691 --> 00:52:08,589
That's true.

1034
00:52:10,894 --> 00:52:13,226
In Africa...

1035
00:52:13,296 --> 00:52:14,695
In China...

1036
00:52:14,764 --> 00:52:17,824
In the Palestinian struggle,
they sang our songs,

1037
00:52:17,901 --> 00:52:19,391
used our phrases--

1038
00:52:19,469 --> 00:52:21,960
"Million Man March,
We shall overcome," all of that

1039
00:52:22,038 --> 00:52:24,802
